            "answer_text": "If \"major\" is a doubling of energy density, I would say not too close.  Batteries have improved roughly10-15% a year for the past 20 years. Why would the 21st year be special?  You can always find a lot of hype in the press, but keep in mind a quote of unknown origin, but generally attributed to Edison: \"There are 3 types of people: Liars, damn liars, and battery salesmen\" ",
